# Type augmentations for Adobe libs

App code should import the targeted Adobe libs directly (`@adobe/aio-lib-core-logging`, `@adobe/aio-lib-core-config`, `@adobe/aio-lib-events`, etc.) rather than the umbrella `@adobe/aio-sdk`. The umbrella re-exports every sub-SDK unconditionally, which bloats the deployed action bundle.

The lint rule in `eslint.config.mjs` (the `no-restricted-imports` entry under `src/**`) enforces this and ships an inline pointer to the targeted alternatives.

## What's in this folder

This folder mirrors `node_modules/` (`<scope>/<package>/index.d.ts`) and provides module augmentations where the upstream types are missing or imprecise. Augmentations declared here merge with the package's own types — no need to redeclare anything the package already ships correctly.

### Currently augmented

- `@adobe/aio-lib-core-logging` — adds a strict `LogLevel` string-literal union (the upstream type defines `level` as plain `string`).

### Adding more

Drop a new `<scope>/<package>/index.d.ts` file with a `declare module '<scope>/<package>'` block. The action and test tsconfigs both `include` this directory, so the augmentation is picked up automatically.
